features: 【Large Size & Large Capacity】Each book shelf size is 15.7" x 11.8" x 11.8" (40 x 30 x 30cm). Our bookshelf more larger than other normal bookcase size(11.8" x 11.8" x 11.8") and can accommodate more items.Each book case holds up to 33Lbs which is more greater than the 10-15lbs load-bearing capacity of conventional cube organizer

【Excellent Stability】4 x 13mm metal pipes and wider plastic connectors are used at each cube shelf to greatly increase the bearing force and stability and ensure that the bookshelf will not be separated and broken during use. The overall structure is firm, light and easy to move

【Large Storage】The cube storage organizer can provide large storage capacity and various sorting compartments, for organizing books, magazines, toys, towels, clothes, underwear, socks and other sundries, perfect for bedroom living room and other spaces. It creates storage and display space for any area in the home. Placement flexibility as vertical or horizontal. The vertical space is fully utilized, increasing the possibility of more storage

【High Quality Material】The cubby storage organizer is composed of high-quality metal tube, plastic connector and fabric. The 13mm metal tube is 4mm thicker than other similar metal tubes and the load-bearing capacity is stronger. Plastic connectors are made of high quality plastic, wider and more stable. The fabric is waterproof, environmentally friendly and it is easily cleaned with a damp cloth

【Fun of DIY】Double-sided connectors with holes make it easier for you to DIY. Modular shape with simple structure allows you to create storage closet in a variety of shapes to fit in your personal taste, as interesting as building a mini-house

【Easy To Assemble】The bookshelves can easy installation, very simple structure, parts are easy to classify and assembly and be repeated disassembly use, eco-friendly material, can be cleaned with water directly. We have various styles of cube shelves, such as 12/15/18-grids black/gray cube shelves for you to choose

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Read all the instructions first and then do it your way lol
reviews.reviewText: As soon as I opened the package and felt the tubes.. I knew this was a cheaply made item.. but tbh.. I kinda knew that it was going to be on the cheap side for what I paid.I cant complain. A few recommendations: read the instructions fully before starting to try and put it together .. I would have assembled the entire thing straight up had I not checked out the instructions all the way to the end and seen the second way to arrange it. 2nd... use the hammer... it's definitely a cheap hammer but it works for what is needed... I saw a good amount of reviews with pictures of the thing falling apart when they put stuff on it... I have books.. dvds.. my record player.. and some other things as it can be seen on the photos... and the thing holds up pretty nicely ... and 3rd. Take your time.. I had to make myself slow down when I got about halfway done and started trying to get it done.... I started putting things on backwards and having to take then off and re do them a few times...I'm happy with my purchase and probably would get it again of I had to or needed another one and the best thing about the whole thing is that my books finally got out of those boxes and have a home. I had enough space for all of them and still have space for other things .. probably going to use it for my yarn and crocheting supplies.Did not have problems with missing parts like other reviews mentioned and had not problem with the thing keeping tight and together (use the hammer)We will see how long it holds up.Hope this helps.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Wasn’t sure how this bookshelf is going to go. It felt flimsy, however, building was easy and it is holding everything without bending. I’m happy with the purchase and will buy another one.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 4, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I wouldn't buy this product again. It is flimsy, hard to put together, and it didn't attach to the wall with any security. The picture made it look a lot better than it was in real life. I buy a lot of things from Amazon, but this is one that I would never buy again. I bought it for kitchen appliances and for cook books, and it won't hold up to the job. I wasted my money!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Very flimsy, didn’t last long before falling apart
reviews.reviewText: At first this was a promising purchase to help my daughter keep her things organized. It was easy to set up and had all parts it also came with a couple spare pieces. Every part feels cheap and flimsy. It looked nice at first. It didn’t last a month before it started falling apart and the bars fall out of place then if you try to put it back together other bars fall out so you have to take the whole thing apart and the plastic parts started to crack, so I don’t think the weight support was accurate. We had small bins of Barbie’s/lol dolls on the bottom shelves then clothes on the upper shelves nothing crazy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars We really like it
reviews.reviewText: We have had this shelf for about a month now almost 2. It is in my daughters room and she has clothe drawers in all the cubbies holding all her clothes and other things like books and toys. First putting it together I was worried it wasn’t going to hold up. It seemed cheap. But we got it all together and mounted to the wall and it’s actually very steady. She also put her sound bar and other items on top and it’s not leaning or bending or coming apart at all. She loves it bc it does not take up a lot of space but holds everything she needs it to. So I ordered 2 more, one for our mud room and one for our other kids room. I would definitely recommend it, just make sure you mount it to the wall in studs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Good product, but flimsy overall
reviews.reviewText: So after opening the box I was a bit concerned. That should have been the 1st red flag!!Assembly was super easy & fast but I realized all too soon how flimsy it is. Once assembled, you can ONLY lift it into place. Any slight movement, such a pulling/pushing on it will cause it to collapse. Red flag #2....I've had to warn my boys about it collapsing several time & when they don't listen, I have to disassemble & reassemble it. It a great product once it's assembled & left alone, but if ever moved, it's a headache!!I'm currently looking into finding some kind of permanent adhesive I could use to keep it more solid. But that's my 2 cents on the matter. Hope this review helps.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great, flexible shelving unit
reviews.reviewText: I carefully looked at how this assembled, as I've bought others that were really difficult. This one came together easily and because it's up to the owner how to arrange it, I was able to fit it in a difficult spot, my double-door closest. I recommend this product!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Toy Room Clean Up
reviews.reviewText: After reading reviews when deciding to buy a shelving unit for my kids play room, I settled on the REIBII Bookshelf. The variations you can build interested me the most! I was able to put the unit together 100% by myself in about 30 minutes. Once assembled I could move the unit with one hand, it was very light. It comes with a wall strap to hold to wall for safety. It also came with a pair of gloves and wooden hammer. The instructions provided show the additional ways to put the shelf together and how many of each wall panel and metal rod you would need.
